Over the last few years, several heads of local government in Limpopo have treated themselves to a bevvy of million-rand motors on the taxpayer’s tab. City Press report that cars for 11 politicians have been paid for with around R8 million of public funds. The findings were revealed after DA Provincial Leader Jacques Smalle took his enquiries to the provincial Parliament. The response raised a few eyebrows and revealed what swanky vehicles belong to each departmental chief. However, there are a few who have behaved themselves. Namely, Rob Tooley. The MEC for finance spent just under R750 000 on his Toyota Lexus. But how did the rest of them get on? The following numbers refer to cars bought between the 2015/16 and 2016/17 financial years: Car: 6.4 litre Jeep Grand Cherokee.
Cost: R1.2 million.
Add-ons: Smash and Grab film, black paint job, extended maintenance plan –
R77 830. Car: Three-litre V6 Range Rover Sport.
Cost: R1.2 million.
Add-ons: Alloy sparkle silver wheels, double locking, rearview camera, various –
R87 872. Car: Mercedes-Benz ML 350.
Cost: R941 513.
